transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yes, sir, I was calling to discontinue or cancel my prescription with you folks.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: One moment.

Speaker 2: Let me pull up your account.

Speaker 1: Is your name Dave Scott?

Speaker 2: Yes, it is.

Speaker 1: Alrighty.

Speaker 2: Alrighty.

Speaker 1: Do you mind if I ask why it is you're canceling today?

Speaker 2: I don't normally use this stuff, and I wanted to try it the first time, and I didn't realize I was signing up for a monthly prescription, but I don't need anymore, that's for sure.

Speaker 1: Well, yeah, it's totally up to you.

Speaker 2: You don't have to get it monthly.

Speaker 1: You can even order as needed if that works better.

Speaker 2: That's probably the way I'd like to change it if I end up running out of this stuff, although I have two months' worth of supplies here.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, so basically we just keep your prescription open for about five months, and you would have to call in for your next refill in that time.

Speaker 2: Yeah, if you could change it to that, that'd be great.

Speaker 1: Okie dokie.

Speaker 2: I will make that change for you now.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You're very welcome, sir.

Speaker 2: You have a great day.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.
